  "body": "### Description\n\nI'm working on a token CLI for Keycloak that can be useful for developers to understand tokens and flows, but also that can be used to obtain tokens for other CLIs, including supporting for kubectl.\r\n\r\nFor password and service accounts I'm using the `oidc-client`, which is great as it has a lot of features that I would otherwise have to write, but one problem is that it doesn't support [Device Authorization Grant](https://oauth.net/2/grant-types/device-code/).\r\n\r\nI'm not expecting `oidc-client` to do the first leg of obtaining the device code, but would be great if it could support the token request. I suspect this may be as simple as adding DEVICE_CODE(\"urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:device_code\") to https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/053cb7ce662a56830126aae31bc35d15d5d2543f/extensions/oidc-client/runtime/src/main/java/io/quarkus/oidc/client/OidcClientConfig.java#L55.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
